DATASET
the folder contains the images
used for training and testing the quality inspection algorithm.

dataset/
│
├── good/
├── defective/
└── test/

1.good/

Contains images of products without defects.
good/
good/
│
├── good1.jpg
├── good2.jpg
├── good3.jpg
├── good4.jpg
└── good5.jpg
These images should contain:

Correctly assembled parts
No cracks
No missing screws
No scratches
Proper alignment

2.defective/

Contains images of faulty products.

Example:

defective/
│
├── crack1.jpg
├── crack2.jpg
├── missing_screw1.jpg
├── scratch1.jpg
└── damaged_edge.jpg

Possible defects include:

Missing screw
Surface crack
Broken edge
Scratches
Wrong alignment

3.test/

Contains unknown images that the algorithm will inspect.

Example:

test/
│
├── test1.jpg
├── test2.jpg
├── test3.jpg
└── test4.jpg

The program will:

Read these images.
Preprocess them.
Detect contours.
Draw bounding boxes around defects.
Display PASS or FAIL.
